`conclusion.txt` is written with score **65**. Key findings: location (home range distance) is the dominant predictor — SmartAdditive ranks dist_other/dist_focal/loc_advantage as top 3 features, and HingeEBM confirms dist_focal at 88.2% importance with negative direction (farther from home → lower win chance). Relative group size is non-significant in logistic regression (p=0.24) and ranks 8th in interpretable models, suggesting the "prior residency advantage" matters more than group size in these capuchin contests.
